This is the first defeat for Gor's Portuguese coach Carlos Manuel Vaz Pinto since taking over three weeks ago.
It was also the third defeat for the reigning champions this season after playing six games, three less than other teams.
The result means K’Ogalo drops to 10th position still on nine points while Vihiga move to 14 on eight points from nine matches.



