Vihiga United coach Sammy Okoth was full of praise for his charges bragged that the win shows that without a red card in a match, they can beat any team in the league.
"We have had red cards in three matches this season and this time we were full house. I can authoritatively say Gor is always being aided by their fans to win matches. The win motivates my team and I am confident with this determination, we can be among the top teams in the league," said Okoth.
Okoth said his players followed his instructions and converted the best chance that came their way late in the second half.
"Throughout the game we contained them and had we converted the few chances we got, we would have won by a huge margin. Gor is a beatable team and our focus now turns to next game against Sofapaka as we aim for our place up in the table," he added.
A visibly disappointed Vaz Pinto conceded that his strikers didn't utilise the many chances that came their way in the match resulting in the defeat.



